<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<!--
  Coverage settings for `dotnet test ... collect XPlat Code Coverage`.

  STATUS: opt-in. The XPlat Code Coverage collector occasionally
  emits partial line counts when ExcludeByFile is supplied (a known
  coverlet behaviour where excluded files reduce the visible total
  inconsistently). The recommended workflow is:

    a) Run plain `dotnet test ... collect XPlat Code Coverage` to
       collect everything.
    b) Filter scaffolded code at the analysis layer (PowerShell or
       reportgenerator) using path patterns that match what this file
       documents.

  This file is kept as the canonical exclusion list reference.

  Per-project floors observed after the test backfill (raw, with
  Marduk + Migrations / Designer / Snapshot / obj excluded at the
  analysis layer):
    SDI.Enki.WebApi          84 percent line
    SDI.Enki.Infrastructure  49 percent line
    SDI.Enki.Core            44 percent line
    SDI.Enki.Identity        41 percent line
    SDI.Enki.Shared          39 percent line
    SDI.Enki.BlazorServer     3 percent line

  CI thresholds live one tier below the observed numbers so a
  small refactor doesn't trip the gate, but a meaningful regression
  does. Apply per-project in CI rather than blanket per-invocation:
    SDI.Enki.WebApi          80
    SDI.Enki.Infrastructure  45
    SDI.Enki.Core            40
    SDI.Enki.Identity        35
    SDI.Enki.Shared          35
    SDI.Enki.BlazorServer     2
  Apply with `dotnet test -p:Threshold=80 -p:ThresholdType=line` per
  project, or via the equivalent in your CI workflow.
-->
<RunSettings>
  <DataCollectionRunSettings>
    <DataCollectors>
      <DataCollector friendlyName="XPlat code coverage">
        <Configuration>
          <Format>cobertura</Format>
          <ExcludeByFile>**/Migrations/**/*.cs,**/*.Designer.cs,**/*ModelSnapshot.cs,**/obj/**/*.cs,**/GlobalUsings.g.cs</ExcludeByFile>
          <ExcludeByAttribute>Obsolete,GeneratedCodeAttribute,CompilerGeneratedAttribute,ExcludeFromCodeCoverageAttribute</ExcludeByAttribute>
          <Exclude>[AMR.Core*]*</Exclude>
          <SingleHit>false</SingleHit>
          <UseSourceLink>false</UseSourceLink>
          <IncludeTestAssembly>false</IncludeTestAssembly>
        </Configuration>
      </DataCollector>
    </DataCollectors>
  </DataCollectionRunSettings>
</RunSettings>
